$ Windows: user access control (UAC)

The *purpose* of user access control is to inform a user when he or she is about to make a change that require administrator-level permission.

User access control can be disabled or enabled in the → Windows/registry[registry] by setting the value of `EnableLUA` under the key
→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Microsoft/Windows/CurrentVersion/Policies/System[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\System`].

